We didn’t even like the way the food was packed.  Within the takeout container, they covered the sides with a sheet of wax paper and placed the fried fish on top.   The drinks we ordered, two cans of Ginger Ale, weren’t cold.  In addition, the requested sides for each individual dinner weren’t placed with each order.  One dinner was supposed to have potato salad and collards.  The other was supposed to have the macaroni and chess with the corn. They mixed up everything! We will not go back to this restaurant!

This is my first time ordering from the soul spot. I read through many reviews before I decided to order, there were some mixed reviews but I figured I’ll give it a try. I ordered four meals and some drinks which totaled to over $70 with drinks. I requested all white meat  which is an option on door dash. Upon receiving my order I did not have any white meat in any of my meals. I immediately called the restaurant to explain what happened. I was greeted with a person who claimed they couldn’t find my order at first and then abruptly said “we don’t have that option do you want a refund” With an attitude . There was no apology there was absolutely no customer service and to be honest this is the type of professionalism that is needed for any business to survive  in a global pandemic. Businesses are suffering everywhere and for me to want to support a small black owned business during a pandemic and receive this type of treatment it is very disheartening. I am beyond disappointed  with the customer service I don’t even want to eat my food. If I do decide to eat the food that came very cold I will put another review at a later date. I hope the owner is able to read this message and take note that  customer service is key in these times right now you will not survive !  your business will be negativity impacted and completely destroyed if your customer service is not up to par, good food is one thing but customer service keeps your doors open.

I had a hard day of work today, and despite being a "good girl" on my diet the past few weeks, I was looking for something to satisfy my need for comfort. I've always passed Soul Spot, and never tried it, so I looked at the menu online and they had it all: I ordered fried whiting and fried shrimp, mac n cheese, rice and peas, a side of greens, and it came with a nice piece of corn bread to top off my meal. I'm a pescatarian and I do not eat beef, chicken, or pork. I called ahead to ask about food preparation and I was very pleased to hear that their collard greens and string beans (traditionally cooked with bits of ham) are made WITHOUT pork. Soul Spot is halal! Everything was so good.... so good, in fact, that I had to call back and personally THANK THEM for such a wonderful meal. I think there is a little something for everyone here - delicious food made with care, amazing portions for the price you pay, and nice flavor that vibes with the downtown Brooklyn scene. From the outside it looks kind of small, but don't let appearances deceive you. This is a place to be reckoned with! Thank you Soul Spot, and I look forward to dining with you again soon!

Sent in an order for our office lunch through the DoorDash App.  As per usual when I send in an order through DoorDash I call the vendor to request that they write the names of the persons that each order belongs to, so that when the food comes I can easily know whom it belongs to.  I've never had an issue with having that request fulfilled until today.  Not only was I put on hold for 7 minutes after the request, I had to hang up and call back to verify that it could be done.  She told me that she had other customers to service and if I could just wait some more, instead of just confirming whether or not people's names can be written on their respective orders.  After some unnecessary back and forth, she said it could be done.  Two hours have come and gone and still no food order has been delivered.  I called the delivery guy and he told me that the vendor was complaining about how much food was ordered.  I guess I will take my $200 dollars worth of purchases elsewhere.  Will never order from them again.
